## Customer [/v1/customers/{id}]

This object is the base customer entity.

+ Model (application/json)
    + Attributes (CustomerResponse)

+ Parameters
    + id: 1 (required, number) - Customer ID.

### Retrieve Customer [GET]

Allows an administrator to retrieve a customer record, which includes basic
information about the customer profile, location, and transaction summary.

+ Response 200 (application/json)
    + Attributes (CustomerResponse)

### Create New Customer [POST /v1/customers]

Allows an administrator to create a new customer record. The new customer may
either be a guest or full customer and the creator is given the option of
whether to supply a password.

New full customers must have a unique email address within their own scope.

+ Request (application/json)
    + Attributes (CustomerCreatePayload)
+ Response 200 (application/json)
    + Attributes (CustomerResponse)

### Update Existing Customer [PATCH]

+ Request (application/json)
    + Attributes(CustomerUpdatePayload)
+ Response 200 (application/json)
    + Attributes (CustomerResponse)

### View Cart [GET /v1/customers/{id}/cart]

+ Response 200 (application/json)
    + Attributes (FullOrder)


### Enable / Disable [POST /v1/customers/{id}/disable]

+ Parameters
    + id: 1 (required, number)
+ Request (application/json)
	+ Attributes(CustomerToggleDisablePayload)
+ Response 200 (application/json)
    + Attributes (CustomerResponse)

### Add To / Remove From Blacklist [POST /v1/customers/{id}/blacklist]

+ Parameters
    + id: 1 (required, number)
+ Request (application/json)
    + Attributes(CustomerToggleBlacklistPayload)
+ Response 200 (application/json)
